# ============================================================
# Theatre Booking App — Frontend Environment Variables
# ============================================================
#
# This file is a TEMPLATE. To use it:
#   1. Copy this file to ".env" in the same folder
#   2. Uncomment and fill in only the variables you need
#
# In normal development you do NOT need a .env file at all.
# The app auto-detects the backend IP from the Expo Metro
# bundler, so it works on home WiFi, university WiFi, hotspot,
# etc. without any changes.
#
# Use .env ONLY when:
#   - You want to point the app at a specific backend (staging,
#     production, a teammate's machine, etc.)
#   - You are running on a network where the device cannot reach
#     the Metro host (rare — e.g. networks with client isolation)
#   - You are building a production app (eas build) and need a
#     fixed API URL
#
# All variables MUST start with EXPO_PUBLIC_ to be exposed to the
# app at build time. See: https://docs.expo.dev/guides/environment-variables/
# ============================================================

# Override the auto-detected API base URL.
# Format: http://<host>:<port>   (no trailing slash)
# Examples:
#   EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://192.168.1.226:5000
#   EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=https://api.theatre-app.com

# EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=
